<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.236807>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Tapiena sakaerat sp. n.: habitus of male holotype in lateral view (A); head and pronotum in lateral view (B); male tegmen in dorsal view (C); stridulatory file of left tegmen in ventral view (D); male abdominal apex in posterior (E) and lateral (F) views. Scale bars: 10 mm (A), 1 mm (B, C, E, F), 0.5 mm (D). d = dorsal apical process of tenth abdominal tergite; v = ventral apical process of tenth abdominal tergite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/236807/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

